description:
Hitler, Stalin and the Boy from Barry

History Documentary hosted by Guto Harri, published by S4C in 2014 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Guto Harri traces the history of journalist Gareth Jones, who broke the story about one the 20th Century's worst atrocities; the famine in Russia and Ukraine during the rule of Stalin. Gareth Jones was murdered while on the trail of another scoop in China. Who murdered him and why is his work still causing controversy to this day? 
A Tinopolis production for S4C.

